Weekly Purchases and Trials

In the code below I filter the data set to include only weeks 7 to 15 and exclude week 11. Then I label each week as either “pre” or “post” experiment

df <- df_cust_longer_NA %>% 
  filter(week >= 7 & week != 11 & week <= 15) %>%
  mutate(
    period = as.factor(
      case_when(week < 11 ~ "pre",
                week > 11 ~ "post")))

Average Weekly Purchases

df_avg_purchases <- df %>%
  group_by(treated, week, period) %>%
  summarise(
    purchases = mean(count, na.rm = TRUE),
  )
ggplot(df_avg_purchases, mapping = aes(week, purchases)) +
  annotate("rect", xmin = 10, xmax = 12, ymin = 0, ymax = 1.2, alpha = 0.5, fill = "grey") +
  geom_text(aes(x = 11, y = 0.25, label = "experiment")) +

  geom_point(mapping = aes(colour = treated), show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(colour = treated, linetype = treated, colour = period),
              se = FALSE, method = "lm") +
  
  scale_colour_discrete(name = "", labels = c("Control", "Treated")) +
  scale_linetype_discrete(name = "", labels = c("Control", "Treated")) +
  
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 7:15) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1.2, 0.1), limits = c(0, 1.2), expand = c(0,0)) +
  
  labs(title = "Average Weekly Purchases",
       y = "Average Purchases",
       x = "Week") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank())

Average Weekly Trials

df_avg_trials <- df %>%
  group_by(treated, week, period) %>%
  summarise(
    trials = mean(distinct, na.rm = TRUE),
  )
ggplot(df_avg_trials, mapping = aes(week, trials)) +
  annotate("rect", xmin = 10, xmax = 12, ymin = 0, ymax = 1.2, alpha = 0.5, fill = "grey") +
  geom_text(aes(x = 11, y = 0.25, label = "experiment")) +

  geom_point(mapping = aes(colour = treated), show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(colour = treated, linetype = treated, colour = period),
              se = FALSE, method = "lm") +
  
  scale_colour_discrete(name = "", labels = c("Control", "Treated")) +
  scale_linetype_discrete(name = "", labels = c("Control", "Treated")) +
  
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 7:15) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1.2, 0.1), limits = c(0, 1.2), expand = c(0,0)) +
  
  labs(title = "Average Weekly Trials",
       y = "Average Trials",
       x = "Week") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank())

Total Weekly Purchases

df_total_purchases <- df %>%
  group_by(treated, week, period) %>%
  summarise(
    purchases = sum(count, na.rm = TRUE),
  )
ggplot(df_total_purchases, mapping = aes(week, purchases)) +
  geom_vline(mapping = aes(colour = experiment_label),
             xintercept = 11, color = "grey", alpha = 0.5, size = 40) +
  
  geom_point(mapping = aes(colour = treated), show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(colour = treated, linetype = treated, colour = period),
              se = FALSE, method = "lm", show.legend = FALSE) +
  
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 7:15) +
  
  labs(title = "Total Weekly Purchases",
       y = "Total Purchases",
       x = "Week") +
  
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +
  
  facet_wrap( ~ treated, scales = "free", nrow = 2,
              labeller = labeller (treated = c("FALSE" = "Control", "TRUE" = "Treated")))

Total Weekly Trials
